        "text": "cc <@U05FU0HPZ9T> <@U088UV6MKFE>\nRight now the Ripple implementation uses Websocket to communicate to the rippled. But I think it is hard to make the Websocket as technology reliable. Right now I do not have any issue except when the rippled restarts the attestor can't send messages because I just get `SendAfterClosing`  error. It is not on the attestor part, but in the xrpl-rust.\n\nI'm sure I can fix it, but since we only do request\/response type of communication I think it is better the change to JSONRPC (changing two line in the attestor at the moment). It is more reliable because we don't have to maintain a persistent tcp connection by ourself.\n\nThe drawback, that the node operators should change it in their config.toml.",
